<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall a much lighter-coloured species as in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. quagga" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="quagga">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. quagga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a red-orange metasoma, and red-brown mesosoma and head, whereas 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. anyskop" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="anyskop">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. anyskop</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. robertsoni" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="robertsoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. robertsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a dark brown-black body, and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. quagga" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="quagga">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. quagga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an orange-yellow metasoma contrasting strongly with the darker head and mesosoma; 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. obesa" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="obesa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. obesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has OOL shorter than LOL, whereas it is longer than LOL in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. quagga" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="quagga">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. quagga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and equal in length to LOL in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. anyskop" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="anyskop">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. anyskop</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. robertsoni" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="robertsoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. robertsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; notauli are broader, 3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide as in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. quagga" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="quagga">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. quagga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas remaining species have narrower notauli, at least 5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide; mesocutum polished between notauli as in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. robertsoni" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="robertsoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. robertsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, alutaceous reticulate in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. anyskop" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="anyskop">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. anyskop</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. quagga" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="quagga">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. quagga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; only a single strong dorsal striation on mesopleuron, whereas other species have two or more striations.
</paragraph>
